# Changelog
All notable changes to this project will be documented in this file.

The format is based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.0.0/),
and this project adheres to [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html).

## [V 1.0.0]

### Added
- Initial project setup
- Configuration management system with interactive and default modes
- CDK stack for infrastructure deployment
- Lambda functions with common utilities
- PostgreSQL database support
- Environment-specific configuration handling
- Bastion host setup for database access

### Changed

### Deprecated

### Removed

### Fixed

### Security

## [V 1.0.1]

### Added
- Configurable air quality parameter selection (PM 2.5, PM 10, PM 1) for targeted predictions
- Comprehensive architecture documentation with interactive Mermaid diagrams
- Step Functions timeout configuration with 1-hour step timeouts and 2-hour overall timeout
- Parameter filtering in database queries for specific air quality parameters
- Batch transform callback pattern for SageMaker job completion handling
- Comprehensive error handling with specific failure states for different scenarios

### Changed
- Step Functions workflow to include proper error handling and timeout management
- Lambda function timeouts: batch transform (15 minutes), others (2 minutes)
- Database query logic to filter by configurable air quality parameter
- Step Functions payload structure for better data flow between tasks
- Architecture documentation structure with detailed component descriptions

### Deprecated

### Removed

### Fixed
- CDK bootstrap configuration issues preventing proper deployment
- RDS IAM authentication problems with database connections
- Lambda function import path issues causing module resolution errors
- Python relative import problems in Lambda functions
- Step Functions error handling preventing proper failure state transitions
- Batch transform callback pattern issues causing workflow hanging
- Lambda function payload parsing problems in Step Functions integration

### Security
- Implemented least privilege IAM roles for all components
- Added proper error handling to prevent information leakage
- Enhanced database credential management through AWS Secrets Manager
